{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "switching_neutral_fraction",
    "description": "Validates that dynamic economic node switching works by sweeping econ_neutral_fraction with sigmoid pricing enabled.\nNon-neutral nodes (ideology=0.40) have effective_threshold=0.10*(1+0.8)=18%, which is above the actual ~14.3% price gap \u2192 WON'T switch. Neutral nodes (ideology=0.0) have effective_threshold=0.10*(1+0.0)=10%, which is clearly below the 14.3% gap \u2192 WILL switch.\nThis cleanly isolates the neutral fraction effect: only the neutral nodes switch, so varying their fraction produces a proportional change in v27_econ_share.\nPrevious run (threshold=0.14, inertia=0.17) showed zero switching in all scenarios because 14.3% gap barely exceeded the 14% threshold and probabilistic inertia (17%) blocked every switch attempt. Fixed: threshold=0.10, inertia=0.05.\nExpected gradient:\n  econ_neutral_fraction=0.00 \u2192 v27_econ_share flat (~56.7%), no switching\n  econ_neutral_fraction=0.50 \u2192 partial switching, v27_econ_share drifts toward winner\n  econ_neutral_fraction=1.00 \u2192 full switching, v27_econ_share approaches 100%\n\nAlso watch cascade speed: more neutral switching \u2192 wider price gap \u2192 faster pool cascade \u2192 fewer v26 blocks \u2192 lower reorg_mass.\nRun with:\n  python 3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input switching_neutral_fraction/build_manifest.json \\\n    --namespace sweep-neutral-frac \\\n    --results-dir switching_neutral_fraction/results \\\n    --duration 4000 --retarget-interval 144 --interval 2 \\\n    --use-sigmoid\n\nNamespace to create first:\n  kubectl create namespace sweep-neutral-frac\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/switching_neutral_fraction.yaml",
    "base_network": "lite",
